  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat the oven and prepare the sauce for your gratin</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ 350°F/ Gas 4. Boil a kettle.</p>\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong>.<strong> </strong></p>\n<p>Heat a pot over a medium heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> (approx. 1 tsp).</p>\n<p>Once melted, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1-2 minutes or until a roux (sandy paste) has formed.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-1.new-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-1.new-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-1.new-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-1.new-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-1.new-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Build your potato &amp; parsnip gratin</strong></p>\n<p>Stir the <strong>chicken stock</strong> gradually into the <strong>roux</strong> and cook for 1-2 minutes. Add the <strong>crème fraîche</strong> and stir well until combined. Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and set aside.</p>\n<p>Peel and slice the <strong>potatoes</strong> as finely as you can. Peel the <strong>parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of <strong>parsnip 'ribbons'</strong>.</p>\n<p>Layer the <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> and <strong>parsnip ribbons</strong> in an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and top with the <strong>sauce</strong> and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>.</p>\n<p>Put the dish in the oven for 1 hour 10 min or until the potatoes and parsnips are golden and cooked through.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-2.new-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-2.new-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-2.new-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-2.new-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1448.-step-2.new-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Slice your red cabbage</strong></p>\n<p>Slice approx. 250g <span class=\"text-danger\">[500g]</span> <strong>red cabbage</strong> very finely. Use the root as a handle, and discard at the end.</p>",
