      "instruction": "<p><strong>Render the duck breasts</strong></p>\n<p>Using a sharp knife, score the<strong> duck skin</strong> on a diagonal, being careful not to cut through to the meat. Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>scored duck</strong>, skin-side down, to a cold, dry pan over a low-medium heat.<span class=\"text-highlight\"> Cook skin-side down only for 10-15 minutes, or until the skin is golden and crispy and the fat underneath it is rendered. </span></p>\n<p>Tip: by cooking this over a low-medium heat, you'll render all of the fat.</p>",
