      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make your red wine jus</strong></p>\n<p>Pour the <strong>duck fat</strong> away (keep it in the fridge and use for roast potatoes!) and wipe the pan clean. Return the pan to a medium heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> (approx. 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min or until a <strong>roux</strong> (sandy paste) has formed. </p>\n<p>Add 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, the <strong>onion marmalade </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>to the<strong> roux </strong>and whisk until fully combined. </p>\n<p>Reduce the heat to low and cook for 10 minutes or until a thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>sweet onion jus. </strong></p>",
