      "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve up! </strong></p>\n<p>Slice the<strong> duck breasts</strong>.<strong> </strong>Pour a pool of <strong>sweet onion jus</strong> onto each plate and top with the <strong>sliced duck</strong>.</p>\n<p>Place a large spoonful of <strong>red cabbage</strong> alongside the <strong>duck</strong>.</p>\n<p>Tip: any leftover cabbage will keep for a couple of days in the fridge! </p>\n<p>Serve the <strong>potato &amp; parsnip gratin </strong>in the baking dish for everyone to help themselves and enjoy!</p>",
